<br>
After 6 years in the military (including 13 months in Vietnam), I returned home only to be called baby-killer, etc. At least the troops coming home now will be better recieved.<br>
<br>
I was in a band that did a lot of protest rallies after I was discharged. I felt that that was a stupid war and, since I felt I had earned the right, I did a lot to to protest our involvement.<br>
<br>
The current situation is not even close to the same as Vietnam. Saddam, IMHO, is a waste of oxogen and a threat to anyone who doesn't agree with him.<br>
<br>
I've always been an advocate of turning the other cheek but I only have 2. Slap them both and we have a problem.<br>
<br>
Push comes to shove, if it's a choice between you and me, I choose me. It's the same with nations. <br>
<br>
I wish all our troops well and hope as many as possible return home safe and sound.<br>
<br>
I just wish the powers that be could just put on some 16 oz. gloves and settle it in the ring. <br>
<br>
My 2cp.<br>
