<br>
I believe in this Country I live in and love being an American. I can't see how anyone could live in the ways they do in other countries. It just blows me away, and makes me very proud to know that we as Americans do not.<br>
<br>
I strongly believe in our Military, and what they do, sacrifice, and die for. They are the real heroes here. They make it happen for all of us to get up in the morning, head out to work everyday. Anyone in the military I hold in the deepest respect for.<br>
<br>
As far as everyone protesting, war, the French, is in my mind a cowards way out. How sad to see our men and woman fighting for OUR country and see these cowards holding up signs saying &quot; give peace a chance&quot;. OMG do they know just how horrible they look? What kind of message are we sending? Yes freedom of speech, but for the love of your country STOP and grow up. Volunteer someplace, put yourself to better use.  As for French Fries and French's Mustard, they will always be that to me, I am way to old to start calling them anything else. Yes, I was upset that France did not help us out,but hey WE did it!!! They had their reasons for not, it was not all French people that said no, it was their rulers. And someday if they need the US you all know WE will be there for them. Right or wrong!<br>
<br>
People who are doing this are just plain COWARDS!<br>
<br>
Last word from me is:  I am PROUD to be an AMERICAN!<br>
<br>
