<br>
My maternal grandfather went to Verdun as a soldier during WWI.<br>
<br>
My paternal grandfather was among the naval forces at Normandy during WWII.<br>
<br>
<br>
It's always a mistake when history if forgotten, because then we doom ourselves to repeat it.  'Kaiser Bill' and Hitler are so easily forgotten by the French?  I know that America, as a nation, was chastised for showing up late to these fights for right.  &quot;Why didn't you come and help when we asked after Hitler took Poland?&quot;, they said.  &quot;Couldn't America have done anything to save the jewish being killed?&quot;, they said.  Saddam taking Kuwait and persecuting a religious group within his own country is a different matter, I suppose.  Damned if we do and damned if we don't, eh?<br>
<br>
